  "plainText": "Don't Starve\nTogether\nRed Gem\nFood Info\n5\n10\n0\nElemental\n(non-survivor food)\nObject Info\n40\nSource\nDropped by\n(20%)\n()\n()\n()\n(0.02% x3)\n10%\nEarthquake (5%)\nCrafting\nWandering TraderWilson\nDescription\nRetains the color of red.\nx3\nFilters\nTier\nDescription\nTransmute Blue Gems into Red Gems.\n×2 ( only)\nFilters\n(for ).\nMiscellaneous\n\"redgem\"\n“It sparkles with inner warmth.”\n–Wilson\n“So pretty!”\n–Willow\n“Pretty rock.”\n–Wolfgang\n“Red like my heart's blood.”\n–Wendy\n“IT IS SLIGHTLY WARM”\n–WX-78\n“It is warm.”\n–Wickerbottom\n“I see within it the fiery death of a thousand trees.”\n–Woodie\n“Red brings fire.”\n–Maxwell\n“It is höt tö the töuch.”\n–Wigfrid\n“It feels warm, even on the coldest nights.”\n–Webber\n“A deep fire burns within.”\n–Warly\n“Red Shiny”\n–Wormwood\n“Glitter doesn't really appeal to me.”\n–Winona\n“Deepest red, from golems bled.”\n–Wortox\n“It pretty and warm.”\n–Wurt\n“I think this gem might be magic.”\n–Walter\n“It's amazing how many gems you can find just lying around here.”\n–Wanda\nThe Red Gem is an Item used to craft several Magical items. It can be used to craft the Fire Staff, Night Light, Life Giving Amulet, and Purple Gem.\nRed Gems can be obtained from Graves, from Tumbleweeds, as a drop from Red Hounds, from Earthquakes and Stalagmites in Caves, and from Ancient Statues, Broken Clockworks, and Ornate Chests in Ruins.\nRed Gems have a 0.02% chance to be dropped by Tumbleweeds and a 5% chance to drop from certain Stalagmites.\nThe Dragonfly drops 2 Red Gems upon death. Red Gem Deer also drops one of them if killed or if Klaus is killed.\nRed Gems can be crafted by Wilson if he has the \"Transmute Gems I\" skill.\nUsage[edit | edit source]\nRed Gems can be inserted into Winona's G.E.M.erator to power it.\n×2\n×2\n×8\n×2\n×3\n×2\n×2\n×10\n×2\n×4\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×2\nGallery[edit | edit source]\nOld Red Gem texture\nMedal red emoji from official Klei Discord server.\nOriginal HD icon from 